    <item>
      <title>14.20 A New Casualty</title>
      <link>https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-20-a-new-casualty/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-20-a-new-casualty/</guid>
      <pubDate>Thu, 30 Jan 2025 14:34:51 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;main class="wp-block-group is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow"&gt; &lt;div class="wp-block-group is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"&gt;&lt;h1 class="wp-block-post-title"&gt;14.20 A New&amp;nbsp;Casualty&lt;/h1&gt;   &lt;div style="height:1px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;div class="entry-content wp-block-post-content is-layout-constrained wp-block-post-content-is-layout-constrained"&gt; &lt;p&gt;(&lt;a href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-19-health-check/"&gt;Previous Chapter&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;A few days later, an unusual patient showed up at the medical office.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;A pale-faced man with a bandaged right arm was brought in. Not only that, the one who brought him in was a familiar face.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao squinted at the chaperone.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Um, I’m Ujun…”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Oh, long time no see!” Maomao said, loudly to hide that she had nearly forgotten him.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Ujun was former Consort Lishu’s half-brother.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“What’s the matter?” she asked Ujun as the patient looked like he was suffering quite a bit.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The other court physicians were eating lunch, so Maomao and Yo had stayed behind to watch the office. They would normally have one court physician with them, but it couldn&amp;#8217;t be helped. Wanwan-senpai was out shopping while Court Physician Lao had yet to return.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“He’s been feeling unwell since a couple of days ago. Just as his fever came down, he got these symptoms,” Ujun said. It seems the patient was light-headed and couldn&amp;#8217;t make his way here on his own.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“What is this injury?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I was told he got this around ten days ago. A thug had retaliated during an attempt to arrest them.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“A thug.” She undid the bandage, thinking that his fever might have been from an infection.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;And she turned pale right that instant.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“YO!” she called out to the court lady junior, forgetting honorifics.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Yo saw the exposed skin and her face paled too. “Maomao-san, I’ll take over!”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Okay.” Leaving the patient to Yo, Maomao frantically went to wash her hands, then covered her mouth with a towel. Then she dragged the military officer who brought the patient over by his hand. “Please wash your hands. Then change your clothes. Then&amp;#8212;”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao rattled off every measure she could think of. Ujun was a timid man, unlike a military officer, but because of that, he was perceptive and meek. He diligently followed Maomao’s instructions.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Once she was done giving directions to Ujun, she headed to the room next door.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“We’re closed for today. Please go back!” she ripped off the sheets and the two unwell military officers lying on the bed tumbled out.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“What was that for?!”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;She knew what he meant, but they were in a state of emergency. “Do you want to catch a disease?!” Maomao also yelled—but she was probably rational since she didn’t use an authoritative tone at least.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The military officers left the room when they noticed Maomao’s unusual state.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Maomao-san, I’ll lay him on the bed.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yeah, sorry and thank you.” She felt bad for leaving it all to Yo, but she wanted to avoid touching the patient as much as possible.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The reason being…&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“To think that it’s smallpox.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;When she took off the bandage from the patient’s right arm, she saw red rashes.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Although still early at this point in time to declare it smallpox, there was one thing Maomao was certain about.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&lt;em&gt;He’s been feeling unwell since a couple of days ago. Just when his fever came down, he got these symptoms&lt;/em&gt;.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It matched the early symptoms of smallpox.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&lt;em&gt;I was told he got this around ten days ago. A thug had retaliated during an attempt to arrest them&lt;/em&gt;.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;An injury from a thug.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao had heard about the random attacker. If the random attacker who spread the source of smallpox was the same person as the thug who attacked the patient, it goes without saying what the disease had to be.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao wrote a note stating, “Possible smallpox patient. Do not enter,” and stuck it on the entrance of the medical office. She also locked the door from the inside for good measure.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I’ve laid him down.” Yo was back.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yo, change into this.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes.” Yo threw off her top and put on the article of clothing Maomao handed her. It was an apron used by court physicians. Although Yo herself wouldn’t get infected, it was important for her to not infect others by walking past them.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I have changed my clothes just the way you told me. Can you please give me an explanation as to what is going on?” Ujun, the one who brought in the patient, looked bewildered. He also had a cloth covering his mouth.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;This was a situation where being kind had backfired on him.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;In a sense, the fact that it was this man saved us the trouble.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao and Yo wouldn’t have stood chance if it were a hotblooded person.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“There is a high chance that the patient has the pox. You might also get infected since you were the one who brought him here.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“…” Ujun looked more thoughtful than panicked. “By the pox, do you mean &lt;em&gt;that smallpox&lt;/em&gt;?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“It’s the one that’s not chickenpox.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Ujun looked drained. Since he normally didn’t have much drive, you could say that there was no change. “This is very troubling, but it can’t be helped in this case. What should I do after this?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“It will depend on whether the patient has smallpox or not. We’ll quarantine ourselves for the time being. It’ll be between ten days to half a month. Also, have you caught smallpox before?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I’ve caught chickenpox before.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao couldn’t see anything resembling pockmarks on Ujun’s skin. “How much do you know about smallpox?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“That it is an extremely infectious disease with a high fatality rate. I’ve also heard that you’d easily get scarring from blisters on your skin.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The knowledge was satisfactory for a layman.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It was truly a relief that it was Ujun who brought the patient over.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Are there any military officers who had been in close contact with him? Any who sleep with him in the same room? And if I could also get some idea of his family structure…”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Um.” Ujun crossed his arms. “I believe he lives alone. He’s not really the type that does well with living with others, so I think he lives in a rented house nearby instead of the dorms. As for meals, he doesn’t go to restaurants but brings back takeaway from food stands.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“You’re well-informed.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes. Surprisingly, he craves company, so he speaks a lot to someone like me.” Ujun was a delicate man, but conversely he lowered people’s guard. He might be a subspecies of the quack doctor from the inner palace.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao listened to Ujun as she noted it down on a piece of paper.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;In the meantime, Yo handled the smallpox with a practised hand.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;While she was talking to Ujun about various things, there was a knock on the door from outside.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&lt;em&gt;What on earth happened?!&lt;/em&gt;”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The voice belonged to Court Physician Ri.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Exactly what I wrote on the notice. I have more information.” Maomao slid her notes under the door. “We have yet to determine if the sleeping patient has smallpox for sure, but could I have gone too far with my decision?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&lt;em&gt;No, it’s fine. Court Physician Lao would probably have done the same&lt;/em&gt;.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;If this was just Maomao getting ahead of herself, it was fine.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&lt;em&gt;However, we can’t have you occupy the medical office for days, so we’ll arrange for another room and have you move over right after&lt;/em&gt;.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Understood. For the time being, we are hungry, so can you provide us one patient diet and three portions each of appetisers that sound good on top of prawn fried rice, &lt;a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dim_sum#Meats"&gt;sweet-salty steamed spare ribs&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dim_sum#Rice"&gt;lotus leaf wrapped chicken&lt;/a&gt;?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&lt;em&gt;&amp;#8230;Does it have to be that menu?&lt;/em&gt;”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;There was scepticism mixed in Court Physician Ri’s tone.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes, we might be with the originator of the disease. So we’ll need proper nutrition to not lose to it,” Maomao said in a tough voice so that the person on the other side of the door could hear it. “We also want some fruits.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“And some persimmons too, please.” Yo added to the order.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“It’ll be great if we can get books,” Ujun also said, shrewdly. “Around ten popular books.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&amp;#8230;&lt;em&gt;Got it&lt;/em&gt;.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Following Court Physician Ri’s astounded voice, there was the sound of footsteps leaving the medical office..&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" /&gt;    &lt;p class="has-text-align-left"&gt;&lt;sup&gt;T/N:&lt;/sup&gt; &lt;sup&gt;Happy year of the snake!&lt;/sup&gt; &lt;sup&gt;And I love how Maomao just ordered a bunch of &lt;a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yum_cha"&gt;yum cha&lt;/a&gt; dishes. I want some now.&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="has-text-align-right"&gt;(&lt;a href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-21-attenuation/"&gt;Next Chapter&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;div id="jp-post-flair" class="sharedaddy sd-like-enabled"&gt;&lt;div class="sharedaddy sd-sharing-enabled"&gt;&lt;div class="robots-nocontent sd-block sd-social sd-social-official sd-sharing"&gt;&lt;h3 class="sd-title"&gt;Share this:&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="sd-content"&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li class="share-facebook"&gt;&lt;div class="fb-share-button" data-href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-20-a-new-casualty/" data-layout="button_count"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class="share-end"&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class='sharedaddy sd-block sd-like jetpack-likes-widget-wrapper jetpack-likes-widget-unloaded' id='like-post-wrapper-130534757-5300-67a2142a8bede' data-src='//widgets.wp.com/likes/index.html?ver=20250204#blog_id=130534757&amp;amp;post_id=5300&amp;amp;origin=shikarito.wordpress.com&amp;amp;obj_id=130534757-5300-67a2142a8bede' data-name='like-post-frame-130534757-5300-67a2142a8bede' data-title='Like or Reblog'&gt;&lt;div class='likes-widget-placeholder post-likes-widget-placeholder' style='height: 55px;'&gt;&lt;span class='button'&gt;&lt;span&gt;Like&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class='loading'&gt;Loading&amp;#8230;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;span class='sd-text-color'&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a class='sd-link-color' href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-20-a-new-casualty/"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/main&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/519581f02e9b429b5d35f4e877f50dbf.jpeg?w=200" type="image/jpeg"/>
